      "content": "The advice about hiring a developer isn't really helpful right now since we're in the middle of an incident. \n\nI want to focus on the technical side. Since it's intermittent and specifically happens during peak loads, do you think it's a connection pooling issue or something in the way the timeout is handled? It feels almost random when it's not a clear traffic spike. Any idea why it would flip-flop like that?",
